    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>Ilkley Wells House | Otley Yorkshire</placeName>
                        <date>Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1859.</date>
                        <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>Your note &amp; account has been forwarded here from my home, where I am temporarily staying.— I thank you for &amp; acknowledge the sum of £241:19s·10d placed to my account<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
                        <p>In Haste I remain | My dear Sir | Yours sincerely | Ch. R. Darwin <lb/> <lb/></p>
                        <p rend="left">J. Higgins Esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
               
                
                
                
            </div>


<div type="footnotes">
                <note xml:id="foot.f1">Higgins’s note has not been found. The payment was half-yearly rent on CD’s farm at Beesby, Lincolnshire. CD was away from Down visiting the hydropathic establishment at Ilkley Wells from 2 October to 9 December 1859 (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 7, Appendix II). See also plate in <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 30.</note>
                </div>
        
